The project analyzes three major variables that influence salary:
Experience
Skill Score
Projects Completed
Data visualization techniques such as graphs and scatter plots are used to identify patterns, correlations, and trends between these variables and salary growth. The analysis shows a positive relationship between experience and salary, meaning employees with more experience tend to earn higher salaries. Similarly, higher skill scores and a greater number of completed projects are associated with increased compensation. 
